<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,524,727,786]" box="[151,438,762,786]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,257,762,786]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Plate 4G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[268,430,762,786]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 250–257</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,834,1651]" box="[151,631,834,859]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,244,835,859]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.50 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,834,1651]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,871,895]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium size, robust species. General color black with yellow markings; forewings with veins black except yellow medially on clavus, cells transparent; mesonotum with yellow marking basally, lateral margins yellow, yellow marking on each side of middle; pronotum with yellow, broken band on anterior margin, scattered yellow markings below anterior margin; crown with 3 yellow longitudinal stripes; face yellow with broad longitudinal, reddish brown stripe on lateral margins of clypeus; clypellus reddish brown bordered with black stripe in basal half, long black stripe below eyes (
<figureCitation box="[777,881,1050,1074]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Plate 4G</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, about as wide as width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ of entire length, lateral margins convergent basally, slightly carinate, depressed on each side of middle; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum short, about 1/3 as long as crown; mesonotum large, nearly twice as long as median length of pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus elongate, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, base inflated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,834,1651]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1266,1291]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view small, triangulate with small caudoventral, digitate lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1423,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 250</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[676,777,1302,1326]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 251</figureCitation>
); style robust, shorter than aedeagus, in lateral view with medial lobe on outer lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[561,727,1338,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 252, 253</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, narrow, tubular, apex strongly recurved in lateral view, small spines in apical 1/3 (
<figureCitation box="[576,744,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Figs. 254, 255</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, membranous on each side of middle, stem very short, broad (
<figureCitation box="[512,611,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 256</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective very long, narrow, strap shape (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1292,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
), attached to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[416,515,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 250–257" captionStartId="79.[151,258,1839,1860]" captionTargetBox="[211,1366,192,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-66@79.[211,1376,191,1818]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 250–257. Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov. (250) male pygofer, lateral view; (251) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (252) right style, lateral view; (253) right style, dorsal view; (254) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (255) aedeagus, dorsal view; (256) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (257) connective, caudal view." pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 254</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
